
INTRODUCTION

This project focuses on developing digital literacy skills required for students in today’s digital world. It covers online presence, communication, collaboration tools, and cybersecurity awareness.

TASK 1

I created an infographic using Canva to explain digital literacy concepts such as online safety and digital tools. The process was interesting as it involved visual design. The main challenge was selecting relevant content.

TASK 2

For this task, I created and updated my profiles on GitHub and LinkedIn to establish a professional digital presence. GitHub is primarily used for showcasing projects, managing code, and collaborating with others, making it an essential platform for students in technical fields. I created a profile README that includes my name, academic details, and a brief description of my learning goals.

On LinkedIn, I added my education details, including my current degree, institution, and expected graduation year. LinkedIn serves as a professional networking platform where students can connect with peers, seniors, and industry professionals, as well as explore internship and job opportunities.

These platforms will play an important role in my academic and professional journey over the next four years. I plan to regularly update my GitHub with projects and assignments, while using LinkedIn to build connections and stay informed about industry trends. This task helped me understand the importance of maintaining a clean and professional online presence from an early stage.
TASK 3

I used HackerRank to solve a beginner coding problem and created a Google Form quiz. These tools help improve problem-solving and collaboration skills.

TASK 4

I learned how to write professional emails and maintain proper communication. Poor communication can cause misunderstandings, which can be avoided by using correct tone and structure.

TASK 5

I studied phishing attacks and was surprised by how easily people get tricked. I will be more cautious while clicking links and sharing information online.

CONCLUSION

This project helped me understand essential digital skills and how to use online tools effectively and responsibly.
